<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5920&amp;p=26208#p26208"><![CDATA[
This is a common bug in software. It reads the position relative to the work area (the desktop minus the taskbar), but restores it relative to the screen.<br />BTW, the Wikipedia entry for the software mentions specifically a bug with the initial position: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Photo_Editor">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Photo_Editor</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Mon Apr 18, 2016 7:18 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
